  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this study is to show the frequency of endothelial dysfunction in patients
      suffering from ectatic coronary arteries as compared to those who have normal coronary
      arteries. Should this frequency be significant we would recommend initiating conventional
      treatment in those patients with ectatic coronary arteries as is the practice in patients
      with endothelial dysfunction without ectatic arteries
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
